docs.abstract: Ocean Village, apartment complex in the Arverne section of the Rockaway Peninsula, was without heat or power when Hurricane Sandy hit; new owner, L&M Development Partners, has made changes that seem to make buildings shining examples of the area's triumphant return, but trauma of storm still has residents uneasy (Series: Coming Back).

headline.main: Despite Renovations After Hurricane, Unease Persists in the Rockaways
